LABEL {
  NAME    "ObjHandler_Tank_76_Shooter_Init";
  ADDR    $AFFC;
  COMMENT "(alpha: not fully human-verified) \n; ObjType $76 — Shooter (Thing $10, 'Gray Shooter'), init. Launches the Shooter on a random\n; straight line: a heading drawn from the RNG and a fixed speed, with its gun already loaded.\n; Every Shooter therefore starts drifting in a different direction, and it is the Main handler's\n; terrain bouncing that turns that into the circling patrol the player sees. TankEnemy_Init\n; advances it to ObjType $77, so this runs for exactly one frame. Dual-entry: the +0 (fade/freeze)\n; entry lands on the body's own RTS — this Init draws nothing. See\n; docs/entities/tank/76-77_shooter.md";
};

LABEL {
  NAME    "_ObjHandler_Tank_76_Shooter_Init__Update__";
  ADDR    $AFFF;
  COMMENT "Normal-play body — pick a random heading and launch  [+3 body entry]\n; enemy descriptor $10: HP 16, and a $80/256 (50%) chance of a Health-x1 ($2C) drop.\n; TankEnemy_Init also does INC $46, so the next frame runs ObjType $77";
};

LABEL {
  NAME    "_ObjHandler_Tank_76_Shooter_Init__Done";
  ADDR    $B012;
  COMMENT "Init body terminal RTS; the +0 (render) entry JMPs here — this Init draws nothing.";
};

LABEL {
  NAME    "ObjHandler_Tank_77_Shooter_Main";
  ADDR    $B013;
  COMMENT "(alpha: not fully human-verified) \n; ObjType $77 — Shooter (Thing $10), active. A free-drifting enemy that bounces off terrain and\n; shoots Small Red shots at the player, but only while its drift already carries it toward them\n; and only at a player level with or below it — so it never fires backwards or upwards, and spends\n; its time circling until the geometry lines up. Each shot costs a 16-frame recoil during which it\n; holds a distinct pose and cannot fire again. HP 16; on death it explodes and may drop a\n; Health-x1 pickup. Dual-entry: in normal play ($15 == 0) the object loop enters at +3 and runs\n; the whole body; while a fade or freeze is up ($15 != 0) it enters at +0, which skips straight to\n; the hit/render tail. See docs/entities/tank/76-77_shooter.md\n; +0 (fade/freeze) entry: skip all logic, straight to the shared hit/render tail";
};

LABEL {
  NAME    "_ObjHandler_Tank_77_Shooter_Main__Update__";
  ADDR    $B016;
  COMMENT "Normal-play body — drift, then decide whether to fire  [+3 body entry]\n; $42/$43 = $80: terrain-collision half-extents for the move below";
};

LABEL {
  NAME    "_ObjHandler_Tank_77_Shooter_Main__FireCheck";
  ADDR    $B02E;
  COMMENT "Fire gate — both aim conditions must hold, else fall through unfired\n; signed X-distance to player EOR X-velocity sign: negative = drifting AWAY, so hold fire";
};

LABEL {
  NAME    "_ObjHandler_Tank_77_Shooter_Main__SetActive";
  ADDR    $B047;
  COMMENT "Searching pose ($50 = 1) — reached whether or not a shot went out";
};

LABEL {
  NAME    "_ObjHandler_Tank_77_Shooter_Main__HitCheck";
  ADDR    $B04B;
  COMMENT "Shared hit/render tail — also the +0 (fade/freeze) entry\n; $40/$41 = $10: 16×16 hitbox";
};

LABEL {
  NAME    "_ObjHandler_Tank_77_Shooter_Main__Damage";
  ADDR    $B05B;
  COMMENT "Apply any hit, and die if it emptied the HP\n; enemy descriptor $10 (HP 16)";
};

LABEL {
  NAME    "_ObjHandler_Tank_77_Shooter_Main__Render";
  ADDR    $B065;
  COMMENT "Draw the sprite — pose follows the cooldown, facing follows the drift\n; OAM attr = sprite sub-palette 1, H-flipped by the sign of $4C";
};

LABEL {
  NAME    "_ObjHandler_Tank_77_Shooter_Main__TileBase";
  ADDR    $B071;
  COMMENT "Tail-call the metasprite renderer with the chosen id";
};

